issues.fix:
Add an equality guard before setting state:
```ts
useEffect(() => {
  setLocalValue((prev) => (prev !== query ? query : prev));
}, [query]);
```
Or more simply: `if (query !== localValue) setLocalValue(query);` — consistent with the pattern in ProductFilters.tsx and UsersPageContent.tsx.

